These three scripts can be used (after being properly customized for each environment) in case there is a postgres installation compiled from sources and all binaries/services are not working as expected.
They must be owned by root and added to /etc/sudoers.
They can be used from the terminal or from within the Geographica SUT (System Under Test) java code.
They were used in the series of tests in teleios3.di.uoa.gr for Geographica v2.
